external_knowledge:
Average signal-to-noise ratio (avg_snr) is a measure of signal clarity, with higher values indicating clearer signals; 
'Speech' genre refers to audio files containing spoken content; 
Assessment details include the assessment date, comments, rating, and recommendations provided by the assessor.

sql:
SELECT trend_id, file_id, metric_id, average_snr 
FROM trends 
WHERE average_snr > (
    SELECT AVG(average_snr) 
    FROM trends
);

external_knowledge:
; The 'sound quality indicators' refer to the technical metrics used to measure the quality of an audio file's sound. 
; 'Signal-to-Noise Ratio (SNR)' is the ratio of signal power to noise power, expressed in decibels (dB); 
; 'Peak Signal-to-Noise Ratio (PSNR)' is the ratio of the maximum possible power of a signal to the power of corrupting noise; 
; 'Mean Opinion Score (MOS)' is a measure of the perceived quality of an audio signal, on a scale of 1 to 5.

sql:
SELECT AVG(snr) AS average_snr, AVG(psnr) AS average_psnr, AVG(mos) AS average_mos
FROM quality_metrics
WHERE file_id = 1;
